<paragraph id="8BC23699330EFFCCFF36FCE922A8FB39" blockId="9.[136,1452,158,1265]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFF36FCE921AFFCD5" box="[189,253,771,796]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Notes</emphasis>
: Two obtained cultures (KUNCC 21–10714 and GZCC 21–1085) isolated from the healthy stems of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1A330EFFCCFAE1FCE921B8FC89" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Orixa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFAE1FCE921B8FC89" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Orixa japonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, are identified to represent a new species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1A330EFFCCFD67FCCC22E2FC89" authorityName="Q. T. Lu &amp; Z. Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[748,944,806,832]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="orixae">
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFD67FCCC22E2FC89" box="[748,944,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Diaporthe orixae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which cluster closer to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1A330EFFCCFB49FCCD2404FC89" box="[1218,1366,806,832]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sackstonii">
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFB49FCCD2404FC89" box="[1218,1366,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">D. sackstonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1A330EFFCCFA1BFCCD2186FCAD" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="caryae">
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFA1BFCCD2186FCAD" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">D. caryae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a high bootstrap support values (99% ML-bs, 1.00 BYPP and 74% MP-bs) in the phylogenetic tree. Based on pairwise nucleotide comparisons, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1A330EFFCCFDA2FC8523C6FC41" authorityName="Q. T. Lu &amp; Z. Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[553,660,879,904]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="orixae">
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFDA2FC8523C6FC41" box="[553,660,879,904]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">D. orixae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is different from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1A330EFFCCFCD1FC85229AFC41" box="[858,968,879,904]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="caryae">
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFCD1FC85229AFC41" box="[858,968,879,904]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">D. caryae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 20/622 bp (3%) of ITS, 7/577bp (1.2%) of 
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFF2CFC7821BAFC65" box="[167,232,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">tef1-α</emphasis>
, 17/749 (2.3%) of 
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFE34FC7820A8FC65" box="[447,506,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">β-tub</emphasis>
and 14/590 (2.4%) of 
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFD72FC78227AFC65" box="[761,808,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">his3</emphasis>
and differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1A330EFFCCFC66FC79252DFC65" box="[1005,1151,914,940]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sackstonii">
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFC66FC79252DFC65" box="[1005,1151,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">D. sackstonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 23/566 bp (4%) of ITS, 9/587bp (1.5%) of 
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFEEFFC5C20F4FC19" box="[356,422,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">tef1-α</emphasis>
and 7/773 (0.9 %) of 
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFD21FC5C23B7FC19" box="[682,741,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">β-tub</emphasis>
. They also can be distinguished by morphological characters. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1A330EFFCCFF03FC30201FFC3D" authorityName="Q. T. Lu &amp; Z. Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,333,986,1012]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="orixae">
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFF03FC30201FFC3D" box="[136,333,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Diaporthe orixae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has bigger conidiomata compared to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1A330EFFCCFC8DFC312225FC3D" box="[774,887,987,1012]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="caryae">
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFC8DFC312225FC3D" box="[774,887,987,1012]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">D. caryae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(98–509 μm versus 310–325 μm diam); smaller alpha conidia (3.6–5.6 × 1.7–2.7 μm versus 7–8.5 × 2.1–2.5 μm), however, the beta conidia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1A330EFFCCFB46FC15246BFBD1" authorityName="Q. T. Lu &amp; Z. Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1229,1337,1023,1048]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="orixae">
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFB46FC15246BFBD1" box="[1229,1337,1023,1048]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">D. orixae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is absent, but 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1A330EFFCCFF3DFBC9207AFBF5" box="[182,296,1059,1084]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="caryae">
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFF3DFBC9207AFBF5" box="[182,296,1059,1084]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">D. caryae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
produced. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1A330EFFCCFE26FBC82320FBF5" authorityName="Q. T. Lu &amp; Z. Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[429,626,1058,1084]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="orixae">
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFE26FBC82320FBF5" box="[429,626,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Diaporthe orixae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has bigger conidiomata compared to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1A330EFFCCFBA7FBC92590FBF5" box="[1068,1218,1058,1084]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sackstonii">
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFBA7FBC92590FBF5" box="[1068,1218,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">D. sackstonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(98–509 μm versus 50–100 μm diam), smaller necks (36–88 μm versus up to 500 μm), smaller conidiogenous cells (2.0–4.2 × 1.2–2.6 μm versus 10–15 ×1.5–3.0 μm) and smaller alpha conidia (3.6–5.6 × 1.7–2.7 μm versus 6–8 × 2–2.5 μm). Based on the combination of morphological characterization and multi-gene phylogeny, we introduce 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1A330EFFCCFBE9FB652599FB61" authorityName="Q. T. Lu &amp; Z. Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1122,1227,1167,1192]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="orixae">
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFBE9FB652599FB61" box="[1122,1227,1167,1192]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">D. orixae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a distinct species according to the guidelines for species delineation described in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B68330EFFCCFCEFFB592526FB04" author="Jeewon, R. &amp; Hyde, K. D." box="[868,1140,1202,1229]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" pagination="1669 - 1677" refId="ref8311" refString="Jeewon, R. &amp; Hyde, K. D. (2016) Establishing species boundaries and new taxa among fungi: recommendations to resolve taxonomic ambiguities. Mycosphere 7 (11): 1669 - 1677. https: // doi. org / 10.5943 / mycosphere / 7 / 11 / 4" type="journal article" year="2016">Jeewon &amp; Hyde (2016)</bibRefCitation>
. The 
<typeStatus id="54C6883B330EFFCCFB3EFB592447FB04" box="[1205,1301,1203,1229]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D1A330EFFCCFAB4FB5924FEFB05" authorityName="Q. T. Lu &amp; Z. Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1343,1452,1203,1228]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" kingdom="Fungi" order="Diaporthales" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="orixae">
<emphasis id="B909EA8B330EFFCCFAB4FB5924FEFB05" box="[1343,1452,1203,1228]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">D. orixae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(GZCC 21–1085), did not produce micro-morphologic structures in the media.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
